    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As long as your List is a concrete class, you can simply call the contains() method as long as you have implemented your equals() method on MyItem.</p>\n\n<pre><code>// given \n// some input ... you to complete\n\n// when\nList&lt;MyItems&gt; results = service.getMyItems();\n\n// then\nassertTrue(results.contains(new MyItem(\"foo\")));\nassertTrue(results.contains(new MyItem(\"bar\")));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Assumes you have implemented a constructor that accepts the values you want to assert on. I realise this isn't on a single line, but it's useful to know which value is missing rather than checking both at once.</p>\n"
  }, {
